Tlyarata (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Russia. It is the administrative center of Tlyaratinsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. It is located in the west of the republic of Dagestan in a mountainous area near Azerbaijan and Georgia.
Population:
It is the home of World champion boxer Sultan Ibragimov.
